  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Strengthening Community Support for Children with Disabilities in Zimbabwe (SCSCD) - Phase 4</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">SCSCD aims to directly benefit those children and families who are the most excluded and meet their self-identified immediate needs. Mercy Corps will facilitate improved access to basic services for children with disabilities and their families, providing a fast and efficient mechanism to improve access to services and support. The program will continue to target the most vulnerable children and their families; giving highest priority to those whose access to services is severely constrained. However, under this next phase, SCSCD will focus its implementation in three core districts where Mercy Corps has established presence, including links with communities and authorities:
&#x2022;	The urban area covered by the Mercy Corps-led Joint Initiative Consortium and served by Emerald Hill School in Harare as well as communities in Chitungwiza
&#x2022;	The rural district where Mercy Corps has ongoing WASH programs and served by Munyoro Secondary School in Mutare

In addition, via Mercy Corps&#x2019; engagement of the NAPII network implementing partners, the reach of the grants program can be extended to other districts to meet the needs of groups, individuals and institutions in other areas. In cases where UNICEF has been solicited directly for assistance to potential beneficiaries, there will also be opportunity for those proposals to be considered under this program.</narrative>
  </description>
